name: Ext.ux.form.ItemSelector
doc: A control that allows selection of between two Ext.ux.form.MultiSelect controls.

members.name: allowBlank
members.doc: false to require at least one item in the list to be selected, true to allow no selection.
members.short_doc:
false to require at least one item in the list
to be selected, true to allow no selection. ...

members.name: appendOnly
members.doc: true if the list should only allow append drops when drag/drop is enabled. This is useful for lists which are sorted.
members.short_doc:
true if the list should only allow append drops
when drag/drop is enabled. ...

members.name: blankText
members.doc: Default text displayed when the control contains no items.
members.short_doc:
Default text displayed when the control

members.name: buttons
members.doc: Defines the set of buttons that should be displayed in between the ItemSelector fields. Defaults to ['top', 'up', 'add', 'remove', 'down', 'bottom']. These names are used to build the button CSS class names, and to look up the button text labels in buttonsText. This can be overridden with a custom Array to change which buttons are displayed or their order.
members.short_doc:
Defines the set of buttons that should be displayed in between
the ItemSelector fields. ...

members.name: buttonsText
members.doc: The tooltips for the buttons. Labels for buttons.
members.default: {top: "Move to Top", up: "Move Up", add: "Add to Selected", remove: "Remove from Selected", down: "Move Down", bottom: "Move to Bottom"}
members.short_doc: The tooltips for the buttons. ...

members.doc: The string used to delimit the selected values when submitting the field as part of a form. If you wish to have the selected values submitted as separate parameters rather than a single delimited parameter, set this to null.

members.name: store
members.doc:
The data source to which this MultiSelect is bound (defaults to undefined). Acceptable values for this property are:

  • any Store subclass
  • an Array : Arrays will be converted to a Ext.data.ArrayStore internally.
    • 1-dimensional array : (e.g., ['Foo','Bar'])
      A 1-dimensional array will automatically be expanded (each array item will be the combo value and text)
    • 2-dimensional array : (e.g., `[['f','Foo'],['b','Bar']]`)
      For a multi-dimensional array, the value in index 0 of each item will be assumed to be the combo value, while the value at index 1 is assumed to be the combo text.
members.short_doc:
The data source to which this MultiSelect is bound
(defaults to undefined). ...

members.name: clearInvalid
members.doc:
Clear any invalid styles/messages for this field.

Note: this method does not cause the Field's validate or isValid methods to return true if the value does not pass validation. So simply clearing a field's errors will not necessarily allow submission of forms submitted with the Ext.form.action.Submit.clientValidation option set.
members.short_doc: Clear any invalid styles/messages for this field. ...

Records will be returned in store order, not in order of selection.
